  "author_association": "NONE",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "A user might want to use multiple apps which connect to the ethereum network. However, they might wish to keep their keystores separate. There is security and privacy reason for this (not letting other apps access keys they don't want accessed).\n\nIdeally, a user should only have to sync the blockchain once regardless of how many apps are installed on their computer. This is only possible (AFAIK) by splitting the chain datadir from the keystore datadir\n",
